      </section>
      <h3
        class="py-4 cursor-pointer bg-[#092958] shadow-xl text-white text-center uppercase tracking-wide"
      >
        biography
      </h3>
      <section class="mt-[2rem] text-[#092958] space-y-5 px-3 text-justify">
        <article>
          Juma Hamidu Aweso is a prominent political leader in Tanzania,
          currently serving as the Minister of Water and Irrigation in the sixth
          phase government under the leadership of President Samia. He was born
          on March 22, 1985, in Pangani, Tanga Region, Aweso pursued his
          education at various institutions, including Mwambao Primary School,
          Bagamoyo Secondary School, and Pugu Secondary School, where he
          obtained a teaching diploma.
        </article>
        <article>
          He later obtained a Bachelor of Science in Chemistry from the
          University of Dar es Salaam in 2013 and a second degree in Governance
          and Leadership from the Open University of Tanzania in 2020.
        </article>
        <article>
          Aweso's political career began immediately after college, when he
          joined the Chama cha Mapinduzi (CCM) party and was nominated to run
          for Parliament in 2015, winning the election. He subsequently served
          as Deputy Minister of Water and Irrigation in the fifth phase
          government under Minister Makame Mbarawa before being appointed
          Minister of Water and Irrigation in December 2020. Widely recognized
          for his outstanding performance, Aweso has been given the title of
          External Combatant by his fellow Members of Parliament for his
          exceptional work in the ministry.
        </article>
      </section>

